---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Sialect" description="A small language experiment by Suraj Pathak.">
  <article class="article-shell">
    <header class="article-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Archive</p>
      <h1 class="article-title">Sialect</h1>
      <p class="section-intro">
        A playful written-language experiment built around shortening names and
        phrases in conversation.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="article-prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Sialect</strong> is short for <em>Suraj + dialect</em>. The idea
        was simple: make casual written conversations a little more compact, a
        little more personal, and slightly more fun to decode.
      </p>

      <h2>Core idea</h2>
      <p>
        Replace the first sound of a phrase with the first initial of the
        person you are addressing or discussing.
      </p>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>English</th>
            <th>Sialect</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Congrats, George</td>
            <td>Gongrats</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Thank you Sam</td>
            <td>Shank you</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Raj's twitter is trending</td>
            <td>Rwitter is trending</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Rules</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Use it in written conversation, not spoken language.</li>
        <li>Apply it when addressing someone directly or referencing them in a familiar context.</li>
        <li>Keep the sentence understandable enough that the other person can infer the original word.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        The original standalone page from the old site is kept here as a small
        archive artifact from an earlier version of the website.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
